The paper deals with the problem of cooperative job dispatching in an edge computing network, which involves the optimization of jobs dispatching at all the access points and scheduling time slots. This problem is related to several sub-fields of computer science, including networked systems (cs.NI), distributed computing (cs.DC), control systems (cs.SY), information theory (cs.IT), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories that this paper belongs to, ordered from most to least likely.
